        <h2 class="post-title">2024 Week 34</h2></a><span class="post-meta">ü§î&nbsp;Weekly note&nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-calendar"></i>&nbsp;Posted on August 24, 2024&nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-clock"></i>&nbsp;4&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-book"></i>&nbsp;792&nbsp;words</span>

<div class="post-entry"><p style="margin-left: 2em;"><p>It&rsquo;s been 29 weeks straight of posting these weekly things. I&rsquo;m amazed that I&rsquo;ve kept at it. It&rsquo;s been kind of helpful to formalize the things I&rsquo;m thinking about each week, but I also know that I&rsquo;m not digging deeply into things. Quantity over quality, as it were. Although, I don&rsquo;t know that it&rsquo;s these weekly things that are getting in the way of that - are they like some kind of textual relief valve? Hopefully not. Anyway. I&rsquo;ll probably keep this up for a bit more - it&rsquo;s been super useful to have links <a href="https://darcynorman.net/search/">searchable</a> at least. But I could do that offline in Obsidian or something. ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è</p><a class="btn read-more-link btn-secondary" href="https://darcynorman.net/2024/08/24/2024-week-34/" class="post-read-more" title="Read the full post:2024 Week 34">Read More</a></p></div>
